2hb: 0<br>
piercing: 0<br>
Level: 65<br>
Server: Stromm (newbie server)<br>
<br>
Weapon: Hammer of the Wind  Dmg 17, Dly 23. +5 Str +5 Sta +5 Int +10 vsMg +10 vsFire +45 HP +45 Mana +2.00 Wt Focus Effect: Haste of Solusek<br>
<br>
Reason: Haste of Solusek, this will speed up your slows, nukes and charm spells up to level 65. Nukes come in handy because from 58 they remove the stun component but before that don't even bother using your nukes. Unless it's the level 8 one and there is no risk involved so you can increase your evoke.<br>
<br>
Added bonus: I like the HP on it, it's not the greatest but will work for the time being.<br>
<br>
Ok if you wanna mess around then ya pull out the charm spell, many charmed pets can out dps your group in the later levels. Melee is a complete waste of time. <p>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=482529</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hardyenchanter>hardy enchanter</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#330000>(9/25/03 9:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=42>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Chanter an melee</span><hr size=1> I've been waving my Staff of the Silent Star around for some time.  Always causes amusement when the chanter breaks into melee <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
