Secondary: Rusted Hero Shield (3 days old, had opal encrusted stein forever, still use in heavy mez enviroments JIC)<br>
Range: The green crystal thingy from Hate, also relatively new. I would like to upgrade it but no one goes to Hate anymore. Poo.<br>
<br>
Prior to the claws, I had a tarnished drive shaft for about 2 weeks (2hb, never did melee with it, also eliminated any possibility of a secondary). And the Seal of Thurgardin in range. Before the Tarnished drive shaft I'd had the Crystal 2hb staff usually only wizards use, from ~25-54. it was a gift and I just couldn't bear to part with it. I had a dragoon dirk from birth to 25.<br>
<br>
I was a melee enchanter, then I wasn't, now I am again ands will continue to be. <br>
<br>
Here's my story:<br>
I started in Norrath the adopt child of a high level druid. (not exactly power-leveled, but I spent time stabbing things wiff my wittal stick when I couldn't find groups) so my piercing was high for my level. Then I got that 2hb staff, didn't melee again at all until 55. I had seen the claws, they were all the rage in the caster circles, but I'm not wealthy and the going price was 14,000pp. Completely by luck, I was in the bazaar when a bard wanted to trade the claws for a weapon. I had a Tae Ew shield I was trying to sell to get the claws, so what the hey, I offered it and 7500pp (my life savings). He took it.<br>
<br>
I love my claws. Assuming common sense in the groups, and caster mobs, I don a werewolf illusion (or boon if melee doesn't want) and melee until the claws proc the mana drain. Scryer's Trespass takes too dang long to refresh and wears off too fast, I can't sit down or risk aggro, and pony is too big/scared to come out in dungeons.<br>
<br>
I recommend Drakkel claws very highly. I also recommend grabbing a friendly druid or Shadow Knight to snare/fear-kite to practice with them. At skill 110, and in werewolf or boon, they seem to proc fairly well. Maybe not on every mob, but seeing as how I'd be standing there with my thumb up my rump anyway, I might as well try to get some mana out the deal. <br>
<br>
Manzana <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=grogokasclepius>Grogok Asclepius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#330000>(11/11/03 3:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=44>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Who uses weapons and what?</span><hr size=1> I have always tried to be a chanter/tank hehe. Now dont get me wrong, I know my place in a group, I know why they want me there, but I like to melee when I can and work on skills. My piercing is maxed out now as is my offense. I am hoping to work on 1hb and 2hb next and was looking for advice on what weapons to use there.<br>
